What was vendored (v1)
----------------------
Seven procedural generator families whose transitive imports are clean against
metronome's dependency allowlist (numpy, scipy, pandas, torch):

  ForecastPFN, SineWave, SawTooth, Step, Anomaly, Spikes, OrnsteinUhlenbeck

plus the minimal support modules they need: the ``TimeSeriesContainer`` (trimmed
to drop the unused torch-based batch container), the frequency helpers
(``Frequency``, ``select_safe_random_frequency``, ``select_safe_start_date``),
the ``GeneratorParams`` dataclasses, and ``generate_spikes``.

Modifications made to the vendored code
---------------------------------------
* Import paths rewritten from ``src.*`` to ``tempo_gen.*``.
* DETERMINISM FIX: ``GeneratorWrapper._set_random_seeds`` previously derived a
  per-generator seed offset from the builtin ``hash(class_name)``, which is
  salted per process by PYTHONHASHSEED and is therefore NOT reproducible across
  processes. It now uses ``zlib.crc32`` (a stable, process-independent
  checksum). metronome audits determinism by re-running the generator in a
  separate process, so this fix is load-bearing.
* ``data/containers.py`` trimmed to the numpy ``TimeSeriesContainer`` only
  (dropped the torch-dependent ``BatchTimeSeriesContainer``).
* Removed a stray ``print()`` from the OU generator's hot path.

What was intentionally EXCLUDED from v1
---------------------------------------
KernelSynth (scikit-learn), the GP prior (gpytorch), CauKer (networkx +
scikit-learn), and all audio generators (pyo) — their transitive imports pull
dependencies that are not on metronome's allowlist. See the TODO(v2) note in
``generator.py``: the GP / kernel family should be reimplemented in numpy/scipy
(FFT/circulant embedding or scipy.linalg.cholesky) and added back, since the
TempoPFN ablation shows that family carries a large share of the signal.

No model weights are shipped (these generators are purely procedural).
